Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 26 19:48:33 2026 +0000

    TASK-003: collision metafilter via Tab bang autocomplete + filter clear
    
    Implement the collision metafilter on the bang-as-source model: Tab / ctrl+i
    autocompletes a leading "!" into filter.raw (cursor -> 1) only when the
    "Tab to view collisions" ghost is visible (empty filter with >= 1 unresolved
    collision), and is a no-op otherwise (a second Tab does not clear it; no-op
    with zero collisions). Esc clearing was already provided by Phase 1.
    
    - actions.py: add the AutocompleteBang action.
    - selectors.py: add select_collision_ghost_visible predicate (gates Tab).
    - reducer.py: add _autocomplete_bang handler; add a minimal Â§3.4 selection
      clamp in the post-mutation sequence so a filter never points at a hidden
      row (needed for frame_2 to select the first collision row).
    - loop.py: normalise Tab / ctrl+i / KEY_TAB to AutocompleteBang.
    - renderer.py: render the metafilter-only prompt "Filter: !Type to filter"
      (literal !, reverse-video T caret, dim remainder) when filter.raw == "!".
    
    Tests:
    - golden frame_2 (Tab from 1a -> "!", rows 2 & 3, selection clamps to 2) and
      frame_esc_clear (type "1" then Esc -> bit-identical to frame_1a), with
      committed snapshots.
    - BDD collision_filter.feature + step defs covering bang autocomplete, second
      Tab / no-collision no-ops, literal-bang editing, backspace, and Esc clear.
    - reducer/selector/loop unit tests for the autocomplete and selection clamp.
    - update the now-stale "Tab is a no-op" loop test and text_filter scenario.
    
    Docs: reconcile the readline-support-matrix Tab/ctrl+i rows to implemented.

